ing vertical paths, scope out column cities using horizontal paths. Once I had figured out the safer areas, I could use horizontal paths on row cities to avoid tolls, and vertical paths on column cities to avoid tolls.\"},\"trial_type\":\"survey-text\",\"trial_index\":380,\"time_elapsed\":1571820,\"internal_node_id\":\"0.0-329.0\",\"final_zoom_factor\":0.76,\"blue_key\":\"P\",\"green_key\":\"Q\",\"correctCount\":11,\"total_n_questions\":11,\"quiz_passed\":true},{\"rt\":67558,\"response\":{\"lookahead\":\"At the beginning, barely at all, because I wasn't familiar enough with the interface. Towards the middle/end, I would use all the following routes to determine which areas I had to scope out most, to determine if they were safe or not.\"},\"trial_type\":\"survey-text\",\"trial_index\":381,\"time_elapsed\":1639380,\"internal_node_id\":\"0.0-330.0\",\"final_zoom_factor\":0.76,\"blue_key\":\"P\",\"green_key\":\"Q\",\"correctCount\":11,\"total_n_questions\":11,\"quiz_passed\":true},{\"rt\":406046,\"response\":{\"other_comments\":\"Overall, it was fun and engaging, and surprisingly brief.\\n\\nOn nitpicks, the 10-second time limit was stressful, especially since there was a bonus tied to performance. It would have been useful to have a timer on screen to let people know how long they have left to make a choice.\\n\\nThe P and Q routes weren't especially discernable, so it would have been nice to differentiate them more visually (and perhaps show which is the P route/Q route from the start, as opposed to them showing up when the routes become active).\"},\"trial_type\":\"survey-text\",\"trial_index\":382,\"time_elapsed\":2045428,\"internal_node_id\":\"0.0-331.0\",\"final_zoom_factor\":0.76,\"blue_key\":\"P\",\"green_key\":\"Q\",\"correctCount\":11,\"total_n_questions\":11,\"quiz_passed\":true},{\"rt\":4484,\"response\":\" \",\"trial_type\":\"html-keyboard-response\",\"trial_index\":383,\"time_elapsed\":2049913,\"internal_node_id\":\"0.0-332.0\",\"final_zoom_factor\":0.76,